<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="NAME"
>NAME <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Tk::WaitBox - An Object Oriented Wait Dialog for Perl/Tk,
of the Please Wait variety.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="DESCRIPTION"
>DESCRIPTION <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>A WaitBox consists of a number of subwidgets:</p>

<ul>
<li></li>
</ul>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="bitmap"
>bitmap</a></h2>

<p>A bitmap (configurable via the <i>-bitmap</i> command,
the default is an hourglass) on the left side of the WaitBox</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="label"
>label</a></h2>

<p>A label (configurable via the <i>-txt1</i> command),
with text in the upper portion of the right hand frame</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="secondary_label"
>secondary label</a></h2>

<p>Another label (configurable via the <i>-txt2</i> command,
the default is &#39;Please Wait&#39;),
with text in the lower portion of the right hand frame</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="userframe"
>userframe</a></h2>

<p>A frame displayed,
if required,
between the label and the secondary label.
For details,
see the example code and the Advertised Widget section</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="cancel_button"
>cancel button</a></h2>

<p>If a cancelroutine (configured via the <i>-cancelroutine</i> command) is defined,
a frame will be packed below the labels and bitmap,
with a single button.
The text of the button will be &#39;Cancel&#39; (configurable via the <i>-canceltext</i> command),
and the button will call the supplied subroutine when pressed.</p>

